    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3851307392" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3851307392" />
    <a title="Kristy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/860657-kristy"><img alt="Kristy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1538846310p2/860657.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3851307392?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristy" href="/user/show/860657-kristy">Kristy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/860657-kristy?shelf=would-recommend">would-recommend</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/860657-kristy?shelf=middle-grade">middle-grade</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/860657-kristy?shelf=ya">ya</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3851307392" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6640101438889141950">4.5 stars.<br/>.<br/>This is an important book and I felt like the author did a wonderful job filling in the gaps of Sally&apos;s story with plausible events.<br/>.<br/>Admittedly, my feelings about Thomas Jefferson were forever changed after reading Alexander Hamilton by Ron Chernow; but I think going into this without holding Jefferson on a pedestal helped me appreciate struggle Sally&apos;s children wrestled with more than I otherwise would have.<br/>.<br/>As far as this being labeled a middle grade, I&apos;m torn. The subject matter is</span>
  <span id="freeText6640101438889141950" style="display:none">4.5 stars.<br />.<br />This is an important book and I felt like the author did a wonderful job filling in the gaps of Sally's story with plausible events.<br />.<br />Admittedly, my feelings about Thomas Jefferson were forever changed after reading Alexander Hamilton by Ron Chernow; but I think going into this without holding Jefferson on a pedestal helped me appreciate struggle Sally's children wrestled with more than I otherwise would have.<br />.<br />As far as this being labeled a middle grade, I'm torn. The subject matter is heavy, obviously, and there's a lot of subtlety and nuance to the historical facts. I think this is one of those books that middle graders should read with an adult guiding them and helping them to understand what's happening.<br />.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6640101438889141950" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

