<div id="review_4120183509" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4120183509" />
    <a title="Liz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/706303-liz"><img alt="Liz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1512288226p2/706303.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4120183509?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Liz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Liz" href="/user/show/706303-liz">Liz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4120183509" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11772335392217133017">I loved Kimberly Brubaker Bradley’s other book “The War that Saved my Life” and I was looking for something that would have a similar feel. This is not that book, but it is still very good. I intend to reread it with my kids when they get a little bit older because I think it poses a lot of good questions to think about. I learned a lot and had my view on race/slavery challenged and expanded and I like that. <br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


